Round 3: updated the plan instead of the impl, per your suggestion.

docs/plans/eden-phase-9-web-ui.md section §C item 6 now explicitly
splits the wire-error recovery shape by *mutation state*:

- At store.claim (no proposals written yet) → redirect to /planner/
  with a banner; no form-input preservation because nothing was
  drafted.
- At store.submit Phase 3 (after Phase 1 + Phase 2 wrote proposals)
  → orphan page (502) with proposal IDs *and* the canonical
  banner. Form-input preservation does not apply — the orphan
  proposal IDs are the work product that needs operator recovery.

Item 7 now scopes form-input preservation to validation errors
only, with a one-line explanation that those are the only path
without store mutation.

The implementation already matches this revised contract:
- claim() handles IllegalTransition/InvalidPrecondition with redirect-with-banner.
- submit_plan() routes definitive errors through _retry_submit -> orphan page (HTTP 502) with the banner.
- TestDefinitiveSubmitErrors covers all four named errors.
- TestValidationRecovery covers form-input preservation.

Markdownlint clean. Has the contract gap been closed?
